cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

The paper uses deep learning techniques to generate multispectral imagery of landscapes based on environmental conditions. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to generate the landscapes. Additionally, the paper deals with the analysis of spatial features of landscapes, which falls under the sub-categories of graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO).
